@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: How do we use our labels and the numbers that are connected to them?  #IaEdchat

@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: A student didn't perform well on an assessment test? "Oh, that child is a low achiever." Or, "that child is a good student." When we use those terms -- good, bad, achiever or not -- how does that impact how we see the individuals?  #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: When we interpret data, we ,look at it from our own backgrounds and perspective.  #IaEdchat

@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: Teachers' performance have significant impact on performance. Teachers' attribution of ability influence performance. Data, policies and school culture shape conversations about performance.  #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU:  We tend to connect numbers to labels and may or may not be appropriate.  #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU:  Labels vs. numbers: How often do we see things like "higher," "lower," "increased," "decreased." What is the context with the labels? Always consider that.   #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: Context matters!  #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU:  When we ask a question while gathering data, we can really skew the info with the choices we give & how we interpret #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: I'm not asking for you to come up with solutions. Instead, when looking at data, ask yourself, "What data is not here?" "What questions should we be asking?"  #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: What number represents our success? Are we looking at overall averages or individual groups of students?  #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: Take a look at Iowa's h.s. grad rate. Good right? 93 percent. But look at minorities and it's not so good.   #IaEdchat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: In order to do social justice, you need to understand the data. #IaEdChat

@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: In collecting data, and we say "pick one option": It doesn't give the whole picture, does it? #IaEdChat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: Collectively we can make a big difference.  #IaEdChat
@anngtopf from @IowaStateU: Social justice defined: about changing and empowering others to change. #IaEdChat
